.TH "tty_encode_baud_rate" 9 "tty_encode_baud_rate" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tty_encode_baud_rate \- set baud rate of the tty
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" tty_encode_baud_rate
.BI "(struct tty_struct *tty "  ","
.BI "speed_t ibaud "  ","
.BI "speed_t obaud "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "tty" 12
terminal device
.IP "ibaud" 12
input baud rate
.IP "obaud" 12
output baud rate

Update the current termios data for the tty with the new speed
settings. The caller must hold the termios_rwsem for the tty in
question.
